   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "fd2075a4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "title: \"Limit cycles in 2D systems\"\n",
    "format: html\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Introduction\n",
    "\n",
    "A limit cycle is an isolated closed orbit of a dynamical system. Limit cycles are important solutions of dynamical systems throughout biological and physical systems (e.g. harmonic oscillator, circadian rhythms).\n",
    "\n",
    "## Examples\n",
    "\n",
    "### Polar coordinates\n",
    "\n",
    "Consider the system\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\begin{aligned}\n",
    "\\dot{r} & =r(1-r^2)\\\\\n",
    "\\dot{\\theta} &= 1.\n",
    "\\end{aligned}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "As the dynamics uncouple we can treat the variables separately.\n",
    "The $r$ equation\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\dot{r}=r(1-r^2)\n",
    "$$\n",
    "has fixed points at $r^*=0$ and $r^*=1$. $r^*=0$ is unstable whilst $r^*=1$ is stable. Hence all trajectories (except $r^*=0$) tend to the circle $r^*=1$ as $t\\rightarrow \\infty$.\n",
    "\n",
    "### The Van der Pol oscillator\n",
    "\n",
    "Consider the Van der Pol equation\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\ddot{x}+\\mu(x^2-1)\\dot{x}+x=0\n",
    "$$\n",
    "where $\\mu\\geq 0$.\n",
    "\n",
    "The nonlinear term acts as a positive damping term for $|x|>1$ and negative damping term for $|x|<1$. See @fig-compete-numsol for  numerical solutions that show limit cycle solutions in two limiting cases: $\\mu\\ll 1$ and $\\mu\\gg 1$."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "fig-compete-numsol",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 672x480 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
