   ],
   "source": [
    "#| label: fig-compete-numsol\n",
    "#| fig-cap: Numerical solutions of van der Pol oscillator\n",
    "#| code-fold: true\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import scipy\n",
    "from scipy.integrate import odeint\n",
    "\n",
    "# Define model parameters\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Define rhs of ODEs\n",
    "def vdp_model(x,t,mu):\n",
    "  rhs=np.zeros_like(x)\n",
    "  xdot=x[1]\n",
    "  ydot=-mu*(x[0]**2-1)*x[1]-x[0]\n",
    "  \n",
    "  rhs[0]=xdot\n",
    "  rhs[1]=ydot\n",
    "  return rhs\n",
    "\n",
    "# Define discretised time domain\n",
    "t = np.linspace(0, 50, 1000)\n",
    "# Define IC\n",
    "init_cond=[0.5,0.5]\n",
    "\n",
    "mu=10.1\n",
    "mu_small=0.2\n",
    "# Numerically integrate ODes\n",
    "sol1 = odeint(vdp_model, init_cond,t,args=(mu,))\n",
    "sol2 = odeint(vdp_model, init_cond,t,args=(mu_small,))\n",
    "# PLot results\n",
    "x=sol1[:,0]\n",
    "y=sol1[:,1]\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax=plt.subplots(1,2)\n",
    "ax[0].plot(t, x, 'b',t,y,'r')\n",
    "ax[0].legend(['$x$','$y$'],loc='best')\n",
    "ax[0].set_xlabel('$t$')\n",
    "ax[0].set_title('$\\mu$ = 10 ')\n",
    "\n",
    "ax[1].plot(t, sol2[:,0], 'b',t,sol2[:,1],'r')\n",
    "ax[1].legend(['$x$','$\\dot{x}$'],loc='best')\n",
    "ax[1].set_xlabel('$t$')\n",
    "ax[1].set_title('$\\mu$ = 0.2 ')\n",
    "plt.grid()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c366897f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Some questions these numerical solutions pose:\n",
    "- can we prove limit cycles exist or do not exist for a given dynamical system.\n",
    "- what type of bifurcations do limit cycle solutions occur at?\n",
    "\n",
    "## Ruling out closed orbits\n",
    "\n",
    "In some situations we may wish to rule out the possibility that closed orbits exist.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Gradient systems\n",
    "\n",
    "Suppose a system can be written in gradient form\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\dot{\\mathbf{x}}=-\\nabla V\n",
    "$$\n",
    "for some continuously differentiable, single valued scalar function, $V$.\n",
    "\n",
    "::: {.Theorem}\n",
    "Closed orbits are impossible in gradient systems.\n",
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    "::: {#exm-    }\n",
    "Show that the system\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\begin{aligned}\n",
    "\\dot{x} & =\\sin y\\\\\n",
    "\\dot{y} &= x\\cos y.\n",
    "\\end{aligned}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "has no closed orbits.\n",
    "\n",
    "Hint: write the system in gradient form.\n",
    "\n",
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    "::: {#exm-    }\n",
    "Show that the system\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\begin{aligned}\n",
    "\\ddot{x} + \\dot{x}^3+x=0\n",
    "\\end{aligned}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "has no closed orbits.\n",
    "\n",
    "Hint: consider the energy function \n",
    "$$\n",
    "E=\\frac{1}{2}(x^2+\\dot{x}^2).\n",
    "$$ \n",
    "Suppose a limit cycle exists with period $T>0$.\n",
    "Compute \n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\Delta E = \\int_0^T \\dot{E}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "and show that there is a contradiction.\n",
    ":::"
   ]
  },
